PLACEHOLDER -- replace with the real public key before shipping this package.

This file must contain the PEM-encoded RSA public key that matches the
private signing key on the license server (EPC_LICENSE_SIGNING_KEY_PATH).
Generate the pair ONCE on the license server (never on a customer machine,
and never commit the private half anywhere):

  openssl genrsa -out /etc/ecomae/license_signing_key.pem 2048
  openssl rsa -in /etc/ecomae/license_signing_key.pem -pubout -out license_public_key.pem

Then copy the resulting license_public_key.pem over this placeholder and
commit it (it is public by design — every on-prem client ships with it).

Until this placeholder is replaced, EpcLicenseManager::verifySignature()
deliberately fails closed: no activation certificate will be accepted, so
license activation will not succeed. This is intentional — it prevents ever
shipping a client build that would blindly trust an unsigned/forged license.
